{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RnkUWV9h8iygbVMtdoa4eC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `analyze_group` uses the group's own DQ key. For keyword group, it uses `keyword_dq`, for graph group it uses `graph_dq`. So keyword avg=0.90, graph avg=0.85, diff=0.05. The check is `diff > threshold` where threshold=0.05. 0.05 > 0.05 is False. But the test is still failing...\n\nLet me look more carefully at `analyze_group`. It reads `dq_key = f\"{group_name}_dq\"`. For keyword group, that's `keyword_dq = 0.90`. \n\nFor graph group, that's `graph_dq = 0.85`. So the difference is 0.05, and since 0.05 > 0.05 is False, the check shouldn't trigger. But maybe there's a floating point precision issue at play here—let me add some debug output to see what values are actually being compared.\n\nActually, looking back at the check_rollback function, I'm calculating `diff = kw_dq - gr_dq`. With keyword group at 0.9 and graph group at 0.85, that should be exactly 0.05, but floating point arithmetic might give me something like 0.050000000000000044, which would be greater than 0.05. I'll need to use an epsilon value or adjust the test values to handle this precision issue.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2025,"cache_read_input_tokens":79862,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2025},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f59780b5-1930-46ef-aa3b-e5f15bcaa26c","uuid":"1bce0a4b-1507-4d3c-a2b9-3eeaae651143"}
